OL,4,CGovernment buildings to fly Union flag
OL,5,Cevery day
OL,6, All government buildings in England,
OL,7, Wales and Scotland will fly the Union
OL,8, flag every day, following new guidance
OL,9, from the culture department.
OL,11,FCurrently flags are only required to be
OL,12,Fflown on certain days such as the
OL,13,FQueen's birthday.
OL,15,FCulture Secretary Oliver Dowden
OL,16,Fdescribed the flag as "a proud reminder
OL,17,Fof our history and the ties that bind
OL,18,Fus".
OL,20,FGovernment buildings in Northern
OL,21,FIreland are covered by a separate law.
